{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4fea162e-cc65-4fff-83fa-89edf415c9be","content":"Yes, you'll have **compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** and drops support for older frameworks. Your project targets:\n\n- **`net462`** — ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3 (EOL)\n\n**MSTest v3 minimum supported TFMs** are `net6.0` and `net472` (for .NET Framework).\n\n### To migrate, you'd need to:\n1. Replace `net462` → `net472` (or later)\n2. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later)\n\nIf you must keep those older targets for production code, consider keeping a separate test project on MSTest v2 for them, or conditionally reference different MSTest versions per TFM.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"98541446-bb82-4cf2-ad09-f43493376f40","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"2410:B70B9:484FA8:4D792C:6A03112F"},"id":"23d27453-9d0f-4777-9a0f-15db65069a06","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:35.996Z","parentId":"1fed0ca0-4cd3-4afd-a0da-0228ccdfa278"}
